INTRO                                             You see a noble Lady, seated by her wise husband. She looks up at you with a    friendly smile. "Good day, sir! What may I help thee with?"                                                             NAME                                              "Silva. I assist my husband with the history of the underland, as well as       contemporary issues."                                                                                                   JOB                                               "Mostly I doeth the work of a SCRIBE, whilst my husband does all the            RESEARCH. But 'tis a most rewarding job, for sure!"                                                                     BYE                                               "Take care, fine lad! And please, do visiteth us again sometime. Thou art also  welcome to borrow any items thou feel thee might need from our villa."                                                                                                    She thinks for a moment. "Perhaps my husband would know more of this."                                                                                                                                  SCRIBE                                            "I write down in many tomes what my husband dost RESEARCH. Some of my works     can be found in the LYCAEUM."                                                                                           RESEARCH                                          "Ah, yes. He is ever gathering the lore of the land, its folktales and legends, as well as more up to date matters."                                                                                    LYCAEUM                                           She beams proudly. "Ours art even larger than up topside! Thou shoudst visit    there. It art on the ground level where thou canst goeth outside to the sun."                                           